text.tspan: Almost a lager from organic CaraPilz and Pilzner malt
and Saaz hops. However, Nelson Saivon hops gives it
a fresh touch of grapes, and the ale yeasts spice it up
big time. Oh, it is a bit on the strong side too.
The malt was mashed in steps from 60°C to 70°C to
give it both fermentable sugar and body. It has been
boiled with half the hops and dry hopped with the
other half. First fermented with Belgian yeast and
then with Saison yeast on Muscovado sugar.
"Watch closely." - "What a treat." - "Surprised to see me?"
Le Blanc from League of Legends
